Remotely accessing Raspberry Pi

Find IP address-
open terminal window and check for IP address, using command- ifconfig
If connect via WiFi check for inet address under wlan setting

Check SSH settings-
This setting can be checked via start >> Preverences >> Respberry Pi configuration OR in terminal window type- sudo raspi -config
enable SSH settings under "interface" option

Access from Windows Machine-
Download and Open Putty
enter IP address, user id (default is pi) and password (default is -raspberry)
